The paper deals with image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of genetic programming (GP) and gradient-based optimization also suggests that the paper could belong to the subcategories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves optimization and search algorithms, which could also place it in the subcategory of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
